fields.title: Blast
fields.text: Blast is a full text search and indexing server, written in Go, built on top of Bleve.

fields.title: Bleve
fields.text: Bleve is a modern text indexing library for go.

fields.title: Riot
fields.text: Riot is Go Open Source, Distributed, Simple and efficient full text search engine.

fields.title: Bayard
fields.text: Bayard is a full text search and indexing server, written in Rust, built on top of Tantivy.

fields.title: Toshi
fields.text: Toshi is meant to be a full-text search engine similar to Elasticsearch. Toshi strives to be to Elasticsearch what Tantivy is to Lucene.

fields.title: Tantivy
fields.text: Tantivy is a full-text search engine library inspired by Apache Lucene and written in Rust.

fields.title: Sonic
fields.text: Sonic is a fast, lightweight and schema-less search backend.

fields.title: Apache Solr
fields.text: Solr is highly reliable, scalable and fault tolerant, providing distributed indexing, replication and load-balanced querying, automated failover and recovery, centralized configuration and more.

fields.title: Elasticsearch
fields.text: Elasticsearch is a distributed, open source search and analytics engine for all types of data, including textual, numerical, geospatial, structured, and unstructured.

fields.title: Lucene
fields.text: Apache Lucene is a high-performance, full-featured text search engine library written entirely in Java.

fields.title: Whoosh
fields.text: Whoosh is a fast, pure Python search engine library.
